  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Prevention and Response to Acute Trafficking in People, Mental Health and Psychosocial Concerns in North-East Nigeria, Phase 2</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will have, first and foremost, a remedial character seeking to alleviate the harm and the psychological effects of the losses suffered by the civilian population, because of the protracted armed conflict and displacement. It will also have an important focus on preventing harm and risks of trafficking in persons through various interventions designed to reduce exposure to violence, abuse and exploitation, while strengthening individual and community resilience.</narrative>
  </description>
